    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear the \"long term\" thing all the time but for a shop with like 15 employees, these costs aren't just some \"unavoidable burden\"—they can literally be the difference between staying open or shutting down. do u think there's a legitimate risk that these rules might actually cause more economic damage to these local towns than the environmental benefits are worth?",
