      "content": "The argument that these regulations disproportionately harm small businesses is a common, yet often politically motivated, talking point. While compliance costs are real, the economic damage from inaction—such as public health crises or environmental disasters—is far greater and more costly to the entire community. These rules are fundamentally about setting a baseline standard for a healthy society, and the market will adapt to these necessary changes over time.",
